     1Ôćĺ# Core
     2Ôćĺ
     3Ôćĺ### `assert`
     4Ôćĺ
     5Ôćĺ`assert<T>(value: unknown, struct: Struct<T>, message?: string) => asserts value is T`
     6Ôćĺ
     7Ôćĺ```ts
     8Ôćĺassert(value, User, 'The user is invalid!')
     9Ôćĺ```
    10Ôćĺ
    11ÔćĺAssert that `value` is valid according to a `struct`. If the value is invalid a [`StructError`](./errors.md#structerror) will be thrown (the optional `message` parameter allows you to override error's message).
    12Ôćĺ
    13Ôćĺ> ­čĄľ When using TypeScript `assert` acts as an [assertion function](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/release-notes/typescript-3-7.html#assertion-functions), so you can ensure that after calling it the type of the `value` matches the shape of the struct.
